headline.main: EXPORT PROCEDURE IS PROTESTED HERE; Trade Board Objects to Shift of Civilian Goods Control to Foreign Agency

lead_paragraph: Looking to protection of American export markets in the postwar period, the New York Board of Trade sent yesterday to Edward R. Stettinius, Lease-Lend Administrator, a communication declaring that the aid being rendered to foreign nations in the form of "strictly commercial merchandise for civilian use" should be "handled as before" and not be classified with the shipment and commerce of defense materials.
abstract: Seeks foreign trade return to normal channels, lr to Stettinius
